import { Button, Alert } from 'ui'; import { AlertCircleIcon, SparkleIcon, AlertTriangleIcon, CheckCircleIcon, BadgeInfoIcon } from 'lucide-react'; # Alert The `Alert` in web design is a highlighted box that grabs attention, often used for brief messages or important information. ## Basic Alert To create a basic alert, you can simple use it like example in below: } description={ You can pass ReactNode as description. } />
} description={ You can pass ReactNode as description. } /> ```tsx showLineNumbers import { Alert } from 'ui'; } description={ You can pass ReactNode as description. } />
} description={ You can pass ReactNode as description. } /> ``` ## Customization We allow you to customize your `Alert` component as you want. Here are some of props that allow you to make customization on the `Alert` component. ### Colors Our `Alert` component offers many colors, such as `default`, `error`, `warning`, and `success`. This is a default color alert description! This example also shows that you can use alert without icon props. } />
} description={ This is an error color alert description! } />
} description={ This is a warning color alert description! } />
} description={ This is a success color alert description! } /> ```tsx showLineNumbers import { Alert } from 'ui'; import { AlertCircleIcon, AlertTriangleIcon, CheckCircleIcon } from 'lucide-react'; This is a default color alert description! This example also shows that you can use alert without icon props. } />
} description={ This is an error color alert description! } />
} description={ This is a warning color alert description! } />
} description={ This is a success color alert description! } /> ``` ### Variants You can also modify `Alert` styles using `variant` prop, with those options: `solid`, `bordered`, `flat`, `shadow`, and `gradient`. } description={ This is a an alert with solid variant. } />
} description={ This is a an alert with bordered variant. } />
} description={ This is a an alert with flat variant. } />
} description={ This is a an alert with shadow variant. } />
} description={ This is a an alert with gradient variant. } /> ```tsx showLineNumbers import { Alert } from 'ui'; import { AlertTriangleIcon } from 'lucide-react'; } description={ This is a an alert with solid variant. } />

} description={ This is a an alert with gradient variant. } /> ``` ### Radiuses You can customize the `border-radius` of your `Alert` component with `radius` prop with these options: `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `circle`, and `none`. } description={ Small radius alert. } />
} description={ Medium radius alert. } />
} description={ Large radius alert. } />
} description={ Circle radius alert. } />
} description={ None radius alert. } /> ```tsx showLineNumbers import { Alert } from 'ui'; import { AlertTriangleIcon } from 'lucide-react'; } description={ Small radius alert. } />

} description={ Circle radius alert. } />

Otherwise `Alert` component will not work as expected. } /> ## API Reference For an in-depth exploration of available props and advanced usage, consult the `Alert` component's API reference: | Property | Description | Type | Default | | --------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------|-------------| | icon | To add icon for alert. | `ReactNode` | `null` | | title | Alert title. | `ReactNode` | `null` | | description | Alert description. | `ReactNode` | `null` | | className | Adding custom class names to your alert. | `string` | `undefined` | | color | Customize alert color styles. | `default` \| `error` \| `warning` \| `success` | `default` | | variant | Change alert base styles. | `solid` \| `bordered` \| `flat` \| `shadow` \| `gradient` | `solid` | | radius | Change alert border radius style. | `sm` \| `md` \| `lg` \| `circle` \| `none` | `md` | | direction | Change alert `flex-direction`. | `row` \| `column` | `row` |

{ Alert } from 'ui';
import { AlertCircleIcon, AlertTriangleIcon, CheckCircleIcon } from 'lucide-react';

<Alert
    title='Default Color (No Icon)'
    color='default'
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            This is a default color alert description! This example also shows that you can use alert without icon props.
        </span>
    }
/>
<hr className='my-4' />
<Alert
    title='Error Color (With Icon)'
    color='error'
    icon={<AlertCircleIcon />}
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            This is an error color alert description!
        </span>
    }
/>
<hr className='my-4' />
<Alert
    title='Warning Color'
    color='warning'
    icon={<AlertTriangleIcon />}
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            This is a warning color alert description!
        </span>
    }
/>
<hr className='my-4' />
<Alert
    title='Success Color'
    color='success'
    icon={<CheckCircleIcon />}
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            This is a success color alert description!
        </span>
    }
/>

import { AlertCircleIcon, AlertTriangleIcon, CheckCircleIcon } from 'lucide-react';

<Alert
    title='Default Color (No Icon)'
    color='default'
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            This is a default color alert description! This example also shows that you can use alert without icon props.
        </span>
    }
/>
<hr className='my-4' />
<Alert
    title='Error Color (With Icon)'
    color='error'
    icon={<AlertCircleIcon />}
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            This is an error color alert description!
        </span>
    }
/>
<hr className='my-4' />
<Alert
    title='Warning Color'
    color='warning'
    icon={<AlertTriangleIcon />}
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            This is a warning color alert description!
        </span>
    }
/>
<hr className='my-4' />
<Alert
    title='Success Color'
    color='success'
    icon={<CheckCircleIcon />}
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            This is a success color alert description!
        </span>
    }
/>

import { AlertTriangleIcon } from 'lucide-react';

    variant='flat'
    radius='lg'
    icon={<AlertTriangleIcon />}

    title='circle radius'
    variant='flat'
    radius='circle'
    icon={<AlertTriangleIcon />}

        <span className='text-inherit'>

        </span>
    }
/>

    title='none radius'
    variant='flat'
    radius='none'
    icon={<AlertTriangleIcon />}
    description={
        <span className='text-inherit'>
            None radius alert.
        </span>
    }
/>
